column8: Alliance for Clinical Research Excellence and Safety (ACRES) and co-founders Greg Koski, Daniel O'Connor and Larry Kennedy created ACRES ReServ (ReServ) as a Delaware Public Benefit Corporation to provide concentrated, focused support for the tremendously successful ACRES Site Accreditation & Standards Initiative (SASI). ACRES in partnership with the British Standards Institution developed the first uniform global standard for clinical research sites and independent third-party accreditation. Accreditation promotes professionalism and enhances sustainability while reducing the cost and time required to effectively evaluate promising products. It also supports regulatory oversight and compliance while ensuring the promotion of responsible ethical conduct to make new, safe medicines available to patients more quickly and with improved outcomes. ACRES ReServ was created to commercialize the accreditation standard worldwide. column8: KYWRD AI - AI Powered SEO Keyword Assistant What is KYWRD AI and how does it work? KYWRD AI is an AI-Powered SEO Keyword Assistant that analyzes and generates the most relevant keywords for your content. Using advanced algorithms, it suggests top keywords, long-tail keywords, competitor keywords, and more to optimize your website's SEO. How can KYWRD AI improve my website's SEO? KYWRD AI provides targeted keyword suggestions tailored to your content, allowing you to rank higher in search engines. This leads to increased visibility, more organic traffic, and improved conversion rates. Is KYWRD AI suitable for my industry? KYWRD AI is designed to cater to various industries by offering specialized keyword insights. Whether you're in e-commerce, blogging, or B2B, KYWRD AI can enhance your SEO strategy. How do I get started with KYWRD AI? Enter a keyword or phrase into the input and click the button. KYWRD AI will then generate a list of relevant keywords for your content. Does KYWRD AI provide analysis on keyword difficulty and opportunity? Yes, KYWRD AI offers insights on keyword difficulty and opportunities, allowing you to select keywords that align with your specific goals and competition level. Can KYWRD AI help me with multilingual and mobile search keywords? Absolutely! KYWRD AI offers solutions for multilingual and mobile search keywords, making it suitable for a global audience and diverse platforms. What about data privacy and security with KYWRD AI? We do not collect personal information or store data. All information is encrypted and secured. How much does KYWRD AI cost? Free - however it is limited to 20 queries per day. Is there customer support available for KYWRD AI? Sure, contact erictherobot at gmail dot com for any questions or concerns. Can I integrate KYWRD AI with my existing SEO tools? Not yet, but we are working on it. What are Short-tail keywords? Short-tail keywords are single-word keywords like 'cars'. They usually have high search volume and are highly competitive but are un-targeted in terms of searcher intent. What are Mid-tail keywords? Mid-tail or middle keywords comprise two words, such as 'Italian cars'. They are very competitive and have high search volume. What are Long-tail keywords? Long-tail keywords comprise three or more words, like 'Italian vintage cars'. They typically have lower search volume but are less competitive. What are Primary keywords? Your primary keyword is the keyword you want your page to rank for on Google. It's found in the title, URL, and throughout the body of the article. What are Secondary keywords? Secondary keywords add detail to the primary keyword and often zero in on the searcher's intent behind the primary keyword. What are LSI keywords? LSI keywords are related to your primary keyword and may include synonyms or associated words, sharing the same context. What are Navigational keywords? Navigational keywords are used when searchers know what they are looking for, such as 'go pro cameras' or 'apple music'. What are Informational keywords? Informational keywords are used for searching for information about a product, service, or topic, like 'best iphone' or 'fastest web host'. What are Transactional keywords? Transactional keywords are used when ready to make a purchase, such as 'buy dslr camera'. What are Branded keywords? Branded keywords contain your company name and target searchers who already know the brand, like 'best fitbit for men'. What are Customer defining keywords? These keywords target a demographic segment, like 'recipes for busy mums'. What are Market defining keywords? Market-defining keywords refer to an entire business or industry, such as home exercise machines. What are Product defining keywords? Product-defining keywords specify a particular model, like 'NordicTrack Commercial X32i'. What are Geo targeted keywords? Geo targeted keywords combine a product or service with a locality, such as 'smash repairs Denver'. What are Organic keywords? Organic keywords are targeted for free traffic through search engine optimization. What are PPC keywords? Pay-per-click keywords appear in ads at the top of the page, above organic listings, and are bid for in an auction. What are Competitor keywords? Competitor keywords are the ones your competitors are targeting, saving you time in finding effective keywords. What are Broad match keywords? Broad match triggers Google ads on variations of your keywords, including synonyms, singular/plural forms, etc. What are Phrase match keywords? With phrase match, your ad is triggered only by queries containing your exact keyword phrase. What are Exact match keywords? With exact match, your ad is triggered by exact matches or close variants of your keyword. What are Negative keywords? Negative keywords prevent your ads from being triggered. For example, the word 'free' is often used as a negative keyword in Google Ads.

Log in to your apps through Hardly’s software and with a couple of clicks you can customize the alerts you want to receive at any given time— by project, person, or priority level. You can finally concentrate on getting work done, with less stress. And then once you are done? We have all of those social and promotional pings waiting for you.  – WHY CHOOSE HARDLY?  –  Hardly recognizes that people are dynamic and needs change. One day, you may need some notifications and not want others. The next day, your needs may be the exact opposite. Distracting notifications aren't limited to shopping websites or social media. Sometimes, distractions can come from another client or a coworker. Our app allows you to easily adapt and hone in on your needs for that day, without fear of missing anything important.  — Need to mute a specific client's pings across 6 different apps for one day? One-click.  — Need to prioritize everything on one project but mute the others? One or two clicks.  — Want to mute everything except your mom? Cool. We'll let in your mom's social pings, her emails, her texts and hold everything else. "BACK UP, WHY DO I CARE?" 23 mins are lost for every distraction and that adds up to 5 weeks a year— poof! But turning off all notifications is a luxury for bosses and independent workers (aka, not a realistic option for most). Alert fatigue has been a frequently discussed issue in the healthcare and emergency worker industry, but no one has addressed alert fatigue for collaborative desk workers. And current focus apps don’t take into account people’s changing priorities and needs for work and life— they are all cold turkey. You either get all notifications or none.
